  "prompt": "Can I directly get an admission in 12th (Arts) after 10th (Maharashtra)?",
  "response": "Yes, you can directly get admission in 12th (Arts) after completing your 10th standard in Maharashtra. Here\u2019s how the process typically works:\n\n1. **Passing 10th Standard**: After completing and passing your 10th standard (SSC) examination conducted by the Maharashtra State Board of Secondary and Higher Secondary Education (MSBSHSE), you are eligible to apply for admission to 11th standard.\n\n2. **Choosing Arts Stream**: When applying for 11th standard, you can choose the Arts stream (Humanities) as your preferred field of study. The Arts stream typically includes subjects like History, Political Science, Geography, Economics, Sociology, Psychology, and optional subjects like languages or fine arts.\n\n3. **Admission Process**:  \n   - Most schools in Maharashtra offer admissions to 11th standard based on merit (your 10th standard marks).  \n   - You need to fill out an application form for admission to 11th standard (Arts) at your preferred school or college.  \n   - Some schools may conduct an entrance test or interview, but this is not common for the Arts stream.\n\n4. **Documents Required**:  \n   - 10th standard mark sheet and passing certificate.  \n   - Transfer Certificate (TC) from your previous school.  \n   - Migration Certificate (if applicable).  \n   - Aadhaar card and other identification documents.  \n   - Recent passport-sized photographs.\n\n5. **From 11th to 12th**: After successfully completing 11th standard in the Arts stream, you will automatically progress to 12th standard (HSC) in the same stream.\n\n6. **Board Examination**: In 12th standard, you will appear for the HSC (Higher Secondary Certificate) examination conducted by the MSBSHSE.\n\nMake sure to check the specific admission guidelines of the school or college you wish to apply to, as requirements may vary slightly. Good luck!",
